\subsection{Method \code{compute_confidence_interval_rand()}}{
Computes a randomization-based confidence interval via Zhang's combined test.
For matched pairs the sign-flip randomization test is used; for reservoir subjects
the permutation test is used. The two component p-values are combined with
Fisher's chi-squared statistic and the CI boundary is found by bisection.
\subsection{Usage}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="r">}}\preformatted{SeqDesignInferenceAbstractQuantileRandCI$compute_confidence_interval_rand(
  alpha = 0.05,
  nsim_exact_test = 499,
  pval_epsilon = 0.005,
  show_progress = TRUE
)}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}

\subsection{Arguments}{
\if{html}{\out{<div class="arguments">}}
\describe{
\item{\code{alpha}}{The confidence level is 1 - \code{alpha}. Default \code{0.05}.}

\item{\code{nsim_exact_test}}{Number of random sign-flips / permutations per boundary evaluation. Default \code{499}.}

\item{\code{pval_epsilon}}{Bisection convergence tolerance on the p-value scale. Default \code{0.005}.}

\item{\code{show_progress}}{Ignored (kept for interface compatibility).}
}
\if{html}{\out{</div>}}
}
\subsection{Returns}{
A length-2 numeric vector giving the lower and upper CI boundary.
